yes you can do it with the engine in.

I changed mine out on my 78 without touching the engine removing only the
firewall and the air intake system down to the throttle body, which stayed
in place.

   I lay on the compartment and worked through the access hatch. it takes
skinny hands and many appropriate words of encouragement.  

   trick, it comes out easier (maybe the only way) to the side away from
the fuel fill.  getting that bugger back in with that sealing ring is the
ultimate PITA, give yourself all day 

